{{Politics of Colombia}} A '''referendum on the reform programme of the military junta''' was held in [[Colombia]] on 1 December 1957.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=co011957 Colombia, 1 December 1957: Reform programme] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref> Women were given the vote for the first time, and the programme was approved by 95% of voters.<ref name=DD/>
==Background== After a [[coup d'état]] on 10 May 1957, the ruling [[Colombian Military Junta|military junta]] issued decree 0247, calling for a referendum on [[Constitutional History of Colombia#The Reform of 1957|constitutional reforms]] and the election of a Constitutional Council on 16 March 1958, as well as allowing the [[Colombian Liberal Party|Liberal Party]] and [[Colombian Conservative Party|Conservative Party]] to form a provisional government.<ref name=DD/>
