{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox high court | court_name = Constitutional Court of Colombia | image = PalacioDeJusticia2004-7-9Bogota.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Palace of Justice | established = 1991 | country = Colombia | location = [[Bogotá]] | coordinates = {{Coord|04|35|56.4|N|74|04|31.8|W|region:CO-DC_type:landmark_scale:5000|display=inline}} | type = Nominated by the [[President of Colombia|President]], the [[Council of State (Colombia)|Council of State]], or the [[Supreme Court of Colombia|Supreme Court]], elected by the [[Senate of Colombia|Senate]]. | authority = [[Colombian Constitution of 1991|Constitution of Colombia]] | appeals = <!-- appeals of from this court go where --> | terms = non-renewable 8 years | positions = 9, by statute | website = {{URL|www.corteconstitucional.gov.co/}} | chiefjudgetitle = President of the Constitutional Court | chiefjudgename = {{nowrap|Luis Guillermo Guerrero Pérez}} | termstart = 8 February 2017 | chiefjudgetitle2= Vice President of the Constitutional Court | chiefjudgename2 = {{nowrap|Alejandro Linares Cantillo}} | termstart2 = 8 February 2017 }}
The '''Constitutional Court of Colombia''' ({{lang-es|Corte Constitucional de Colombia}}) is the [[supreme court|supreme]] [[constitutional court]] of [[Colombia]]. Part of the [[Judiciary of Colombia|Judiciary]], it is the final [[appellate court]] for matters involving interpretation of the Constitution with the power to determine the constitutionality of laws, acts, and statutes.
The court was first established by the [[Colombian Constitution of 1991|Constitution of 1991]], and its first session began in March 1992. The court is housed within the shared judicial complex of the [[Palace of Justice of Colombia|Palace of Justice]] located on the north side of [[Bolívar Square]] in the {{nowrap|[[La Candelaria]]}} neighbourhood of [[Bogotá]].
The Constitutional Court consists of nine [[magistrate]]s who are elected by the [[Senate of Colombia]] from ternary lists drawn up by the [[President of Colombia|President]], the [[Supreme Court of Justice of Colombia|Supreme Court of Justice]], and the [[Council of State (Colombia)|Council of State]]. The magistrates serve for a term of eight years. The court is headed by a President and Vice President.
